WEBVTT

00:00:02.022 --> 00:00:06.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our convention program
contains over 90 audio and video productions,

00:00:06.777 --> 00:00:09.864 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
including the one we just enjoyed.

00:00:09.864 --> 00:00:13.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, these videos are made
at various locations around the world.

00:00:13.868 --> 00:00:16.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the days of Ezra and Nehemiah,

00:00:16.245 --> 00:00:19.248 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Israelites willingly
gave material contributions

00:00:19.248 --> 00:00:21.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in support of true worship,

00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:24.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we have the same privilege today.

00:00:24.045 --> 00:00:27.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For your convenience,
donations can be made online

00:00:27.465 --> 00:00:30.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at donate.jw.org.

00:00:31.844 --> 00:00:33.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Please be seated.

00:00:35.723 --> 00:00:40.728 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This convention has clearly shown
that Jehovah wants us to rejoice.

00:00:42.146 --> 00:00:46.818 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is our greatest source of joy,
both now and in the future?

00:00:46.818 --> 00:00:49.153 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We know that you will appreciate

00:00:49.153 --> 00:00:52.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the heartwarming final talk
of this convention.

00:00:52.740 --> 00:00:56.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother David Splane of the Governing Body
will discuss the theme

00:00:56.536 --> 00:00:59.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Find Exquisite Delight in Jehovah’!”

00:01:07.255 --> 00:01:12.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He was an old man,
a very successful one.

00:01:12.260 --> 00:01:16.055 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’d made a lot of money in his time.

00:01:16.055 --> 00:01:19.517 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But let’s not envy him,

00:01:19.517 --> 00:01:24.063 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because for much of his life
he was under a lot of pressure.

00:01:24.063 --> 00:01:26.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His first marriage was a troubled one;

00:01:26.858 --> 00:01:30.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his wife was cold and critical.

00:01:30.236 --> 00:01:33.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He raised a large family in the truth,

00:01:33.239 --> 00:01:37.994 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but some of his sons
didn’t turn out so well.

00:01:37.994 --> 00:01:42.999 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A few of his friends weren’t there
for him when he needed them most.

00:01:42.999 --> 00:01:48.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He lost a child in death.

00:01:49.381 --> 00:01:53.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may have guessed
that we’re talking about David,

00:01:53.718 --> 00:01:57.556 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the writer of the 37th Psalm.

00:01:57.556 --> 00:02:02.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I was once young,”
he said, but “now I am old.”

00:02:02.561 --> 00:02:07.566 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So here is an old man
taking stock of his life

00:02:07.566 --> 00:02:10.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and sharing a secret with us.

00:02:10.652 --> 00:02:13.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What was it that helped him to cope

00:02:13.113 --> 00:02:15.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when everything around him was going wrong?

00:02:15.699 --> 00:02:17.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s find out.

00:02:17.576 --> 00:02:21.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn to Psalm 37:4.

00:02:21.038 --> 00:02:25.292 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the theme text for our discussion,
so I’ll give you a moment to find that

00:02:25.292 --> 00:02:29.713 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Psalm 37:4.

00:02:29.713 --> 00:02:33.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And David writes:

00:02:33.133 --> 00:02:38.138 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Find exquisite delight in Jehovah,

00:02:38.138 --> 00:02:42.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he will grant you
the desires of your heart.”

00:02:42.976 --> 00:02:46.563 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re going to focus on the first part
of the verse at this point:

00:02:46.563 --> 00:02:51.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Find exquisite delight in Jehovah.”

00:02:51.527 --> 00:02:55.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Exquisite delight,”
or maybe you say exquisite.

00:02:55.781 --> 00:02:59.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Whether you say exquisite or exquisite,

00:02:59.118 --> 00:03:01.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we don’t use that expression very much,
do we?

00:03:01.495 --> 00:03:03.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But look down at the footnote;

00:03:03.497 --> 00:03:07.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it says: “Find your greatest joy.”

00:03:07.168 --> 00:03:09.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So David is saying,

00:03:09.170 --> 00:03:13.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Find your greatest joy in Jehovah,

00:03:13.174 --> 00:03:17.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he will give you
the desire of your heart.’

00:03:17.261 --> 00:03:20.973 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that was David’s secret.

00:03:20.973 --> 00:03:24.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He couldn’t always count on his family life.

00:03:24.226 --> 00:03:28.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he never knew
when a trusted friend would turn against him.

00:03:28.189 --> 00:03:31.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But he did know his God.

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:36.405 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He knew that Jehovah
would never disappoint him.

00:03:36.405 --> 00:03:39.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, that’s a good reminder for us,
isn’t it?

00:03:39.659 --> 00:03:42.411 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Humans may disappoint,

00:03:42.411 --> 00:03:45.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah, never.

00:03:45.498 --> 00:03:47.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He is our North Star.

00:03:47.875 --> 00:03:50.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And so when we get lost
or when we get confused,

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:54.090 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when we feel we’ve lost our way,
we really need to look heavenward.

00:03:54.090 --> 00:03:57.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Look to Jehovah,
and let Jehovah

00:03:57.260 --> 00:04:00.805 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
be our “greatest joy.”

00:04:00.805 --> 00:04:04.809 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To know Jehovah is to love him.

00:04:04.809 --> 00:04:08.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what do you do when you
want to get close to someone,

00:04:08.479 --> 00:04:11.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when you want to develop
a friendship with someone?

00:04:11.357 --> 00:04:14.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, you find ways
to spend time with that person.

00:04:14.944 --> 00:04:17.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You want that person as a friend.

00:04:17.238 --> 00:04:21.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And so you go about finding ways
to spend time with that person.

00:04:21.701 --> 00:04:24.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, it’s the same with Jehovah God.

00:04:24.537 --> 00:04:27.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We want him as our Friend.

00:04:27.165 --> 00:04:29.167 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what do we do?

00:04:29.167 --> 00:04:31.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We look for ways to spend time with him—

00:04:31.461 --> 00:04:35.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
reading his Word, meditating on his Word,

00:04:35.131 --> 00:04:38.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
letting it sink deeply into our heart.

00:04:38.009 --> 00:04:40.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then the more we get to know Jehovah,

00:04:40.887 --> 00:04:43.014 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the more we love him

00:04:43.014 --> 00:04:46.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the more at ease
we’ll be in his presence.

00:04:46.434 --> 00:04:48.728 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that’s where prayer comes in.

00:04:48.728 --> 00:04:51.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We can develop a friendship with Jehovah

00:04:51.022 --> 00:04:54.192 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that is so close, so intimate,

00:04:54.192 --> 00:04:57.404 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we can confide in Jehovah
things that we would never,

00:04:57.404 --> 00:05:01.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
ever tell another human on earth.

00:05:01.199 --> 00:05:03.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the good news?

00:05:03.243 --> 00:05:05.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The good news is that Jehovah wants

00:05:05.704 --> 00:05:09.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
us to get just that close to him.

00:05:09.875 --> 00:05:14.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, we had big plans
for this summer, didn’t we?

00:05:14.671 --> 00:05:16.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Special conventions,

00:05:16.798 --> 00:05:19.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
regional conventions
in all parts of the earth,

00:05:19.343 --> 00:05:22.387 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
happy times, warm fellowship

00:05:22.387 --> 00:05:25.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and then the coronavirus.

00:05:25.891 --> 00:05:28.143 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You know, at the end of March,

00:05:28.143 --> 00:05:30.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Governing Body realized
that we were going to have to make

00:05:30.771 --> 00:05:34.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some important adjustments
as far as the conventions were concerned.

00:05:34.525 --> 00:05:36.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what to do?

00:05:36.693 --> 00:05:40.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All of the outlines had been prepared
—48 of them.

00:05:40.322 --> 00:05:43.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the Teaching Committee
came up with an idea.

00:05:43.408 --> 00:05:47.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s have the Governing Body
and many of the helpers

00:05:47.788 --> 00:05:50.791 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
deliver all of the convention talks
on the program.

00:05:50.791 --> 00:05:53.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ll record them,
and then the brothers

00:05:53.961 --> 00:05:56.046 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in all parts of the earth

00:05:56.046 --> 00:05:59.633 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will be able to enjoy
the program in safety.

00:05:59.633 --> 00:06:02.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, this was going to be
a tremendous job

00:06:02.678 --> 00:06:05.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for a number of Bethel departments.

00:06:05.306 --> 00:06:09.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sixty members of the Broadcasting Department
here at headquarters

00:06:09.184 --> 00:06:12.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
worked tirelessly over a three-week period

00:06:12.229 --> 00:06:15.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to schedule and record the program.

00:06:15.065 --> 00:06:17.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And in the branches,

00:06:17.067 --> 00:06:21.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
thousands of energetic volunteers
in our translation departments

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:24.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
produced the program in 400 languages

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:28.120 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—probably more than 400 languages
when it’s all done.

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:32.249 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then, 44 broadcasting departments

00:06:32.249 --> 00:06:35.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the branches also had a share.

00:06:35.503 --> 00:06:40.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So to all of those who had a share
in making this program possible,

00:06:40.341 --> 00:06:45.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
all those who were involved in scheduling
and recording and translating,

00:06:45.054 --> 00:06:47.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we want to say: “Thank you.

00:06:47.390 --> 00:06:51.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thank you so very much
for all you’ve done for us.”

00:06:51.853 --> 00:06:55.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, speaking of broadcasting,

00:06:55.314 --> 00:06:57.859 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
do you think Jehovah has been preparing us

00:06:57.859 --> 00:07:00.069 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for something like this pandemic?

00:07:00.069 --> 00:07:02.071 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think about this:

00:07:02.071 --> 00:07:05.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A few years ago, the decision was made

00:07:05.199 --> 00:07:09.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to set up something called JW Broadcasting®.

00:07:09.245 --> 00:07:13.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And at the time, who knew
how practical an arrangement

00:07:13.082 --> 00:07:15.084 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that was going to turn out to be?

00:07:15.084 --> 00:07:20.006 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And who knows what uses JWB
will be put to in the future?

00:07:20.006 --> 00:07:22.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah knows.

00:07:22.008 --> 00:07:23.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah looks ahead.

00:07:23.718 --> 00:07:26.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sometimes we don’t know ourselves
why certain decisions are made

00:07:26.763 --> 00:07:30.892 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or why we are making certain decisions,
but Jehovah knows.

00:07:30.892 --> 00:07:34.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is our “greatest joy.”

00:07:34.437 --> 00:07:37.023 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And here’s another thing:

00:07:37.023 --> 00:07:40.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the theme
for this convention was being chosen,

00:07:40.568 --> 00:07:43.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there was no coronavirus on the horizon.

00:07:43.530 --> 00:07:47.951 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yet, can you think of a better theme
for a convention than this one?

00:07:47.951 --> 00:07:52.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joy—what an appropriate theme
for a convention!

00:07:52.622 --> 00:07:56.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, some of you have lost your jobs,

00:07:56.042 --> 00:08:00.255 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
others have been very sick
during the past few months,

00:08:00.255 --> 00:08:05.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and a few of you
have lost loved ones in death.

00:08:05.093 --> 00:08:09.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s no way you can be happy
about those circumstances.

00:08:09.097 --> 00:08:12.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But you can rejoice
in your knowledge of Jehovah.

00:08:12.309 --> 00:08:14.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can rejoice in your knowledge

00:08:14.895 --> 00:08:18.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of what Jehovah God
has in store for us in the future.

00:08:18.231 --> 00:08:20.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
People outside don’t have that.

00:08:20.734 --> 00:08:22.069 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We do.

00:08:22.069 --> 00:08:25.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We rejoice in Jehovah.

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:28.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And did you notice
how well our convention program

00:08:28.116 --> 00:08:33.121 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
matched up with the theme
for this year’s yeartext?

00:08:33.121 --> 00:08:35.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Make disciples . . . , baptizing them.”

00:08:35.832 --> 00:08:40.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We had so much information
on how to improve on our teaching skills.

00:08:40.837 --> 00:08:43.173 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why do you think that is?

00:08:43.173 --> 00:08:47.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Could it be that there’s
a lot more work to do in that respect?

00:08:47.177 --> 00:08:50.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, we don’t know
when the great tribulation is going to come,

00:08:50.722 --> 00:08:55.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but we are determined
to keep busy until the end does come.

00:08:55.477 --> 00:08:59.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And wasn’t it a good idea
to have us follow the progress

00:08:59.314 --> 00:09:02.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of a Bible student, Jade, as Neeta

00:09:02.985 --> 00:09:06.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
overcame one challenge after another?

00:09:06.030 --> 00:09:08.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That was realistic, wasn’t it?

00:09:08.574 --> 00:09:10.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a transformation!

00:09:10.826 --> 00:09:14.413 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jade isn’t “jaded” anymore.

00:09:14.413 --> 00:09:18.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And there was
a subtle message in those videos:

00:09:18.125 --> 00:09:22.463 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We should never,
ever trust first impressions.

00:09:22.463 --> 00:09:26.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First impressions can be wrong.

00:09:26.467 --> 00:09:30.346 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, whether you’re conducting
a study right now or not,

00:09:30.346 --> 00:09:32.681 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m sure you can hardly wait
to get back to the field

00:09:32.681 --> 00:09:35.142 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to apply some of those suggestions.

00:09:35.142 --> 00:09:39.355 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a wonderful part
of the program that was!

00:09:39.355 --> 00:09:41.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what about
other parts of the program?

00:09:41.899 --> 00:09:44.276 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you remember
some of these highlights?

00:09:44.276 --> 00:09:45.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s watch.

00:09:49.156 --> 00:09:52.660 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There are millions of Jehovah’s Witnesses
around the world,

00:09:55.288 --> 00:09:57.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
each finding a way

00:09:57.540 --> 00:09:59.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to be joyful.

00:10:01.627 --> 00:10:03.754 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Despite the trials we face,

00:10:03.754 --> 00:10:06.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can find joy

00:10:06.591 --> 00:10:08.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the choices we’re making, 

00:10:12.430 --> 00:10:14.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the families we’re raising, 

00:10:16.976 --> 00:10:19.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the creation we’re observing, 

00:10:26.402 --> 00:10:29.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the peace we’re promoting.

00:10:30.698 --> 00:10:32.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joy is found

00:10:32.367 --> 00:10:34.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the message we’re preaching.

00:10:38.915 --> 00:10:41.918 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah promises us joy despite 

00:10:41.918 --> 00:10:44.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the trials we’re enduring

00:10:44.421 --> 00:10:46.965 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and persecution we’re facing.

00:10:46.965 --> 00:10:48.925 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He promises us joy

00:10:48.925 --> 00:10:51.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
through the stand we’re taking.

00:10:52.595 --> 00:10:54.806 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Through anything in life,

00:10:54.806 --> 00:10:57.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you can find joy in Jehovah.

00:10:58.018 --> 00:11:00.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He wants you to be happy.

00:11:01.730 --> 00:11:03.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His joy can be yours

00:11:03.732 --> 00:11:05.567 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
now and forever!

00:11:07.277 --> 00:11:10.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So will you accept it?

00:11:13.366 --> 00:11:16.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has the right to expect
that we’ll love him

00:11:16.953 --> 00:11:20.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even more than we love
our husband, our wife,

00:11:20.832 --> 00:11:23.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our son or daughter, or our parents.

00:11:23.919 --> 00:11:26.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He also has the right to expect

00:11:26.004 --> 00:11:28.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we’ll love him
more than we love our job,

00:11:28.256 --> 00:11:30.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a favorite hobby,

00:11:30.258 --> 00:11:33.637 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or maybe a sport
that we’re passionate about.

00:11:33.637 --> 00:11:38.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has to come first.

00:11:39.768 --> 00:11:42.646 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Has your desire to put Jehovah first

00:11:42.646 --> 00:11:44.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
been tested during this pandemic?

00:11:44.856 --> 00:11:47.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You lost your job,

00:11:47.025 --> 00:11:50.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you searched desperately
for another one.

00:11:50.904 --> 00:11:55.284 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Finally, after a long search,
you found one,

00:11:55.284 --> 00:11:57.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but it was a job that would require you

00:11:57.536 --> 00:12:01.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to miss all your meetings
and opportunities for field service.

00:12:01.415 --> 00:12:04.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a temptation to take that job!

00:12:04.877 --> 00:12:07.212 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ve been out of work for months.

00:12:07.212 --> 00:12:09.965 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You felt helpless, because a family member

00:12:09.965 --> 00:12:12.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is supposed to provide for his family.

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:17.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It would take a lot of faith
for you to refuse that job,

00:12:17.765 --> 00:12:21.560 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
pray to Jehovah, and then wait,

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:23.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to hold on a little longer

00:12:23.604 --> 00:12:27.191 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to see what Jehovah
would work out for you,

00:12:27.191 --> 00:12:31.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
showing that Jehovah has to come first,

00:12:31.237 --> 00:12:33.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even when it comes
to providing for our family.

00:12:33.989 --> 00:12:36.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We have the example of the Jews

00:12:36.242 --> 00:12:40.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who were returning from Babylon to Jerusalem.

00:12:40.621 --> 00:12:45.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, captivity in Babylon
wasn’t as harsh as slavery in Egypt.

00:12:45.626 --> 00:12:50.006 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jews in Babylon could build a house,

00:12:50.006 --> 00:12:54.844 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
run a business, plant a vineyard,
get comfortable in life.

00:12:54.844 --> 00:12:57.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of them even got rich.

00:12:57.263 --> 00:13:00.516 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Scholars believe that it was in Babylon

00:13:00.516 --> 00:13:02.602 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that the Jews learned about the art

00:13:02.602 --> 00:13:05.396 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of buying and selling, trade, and commerce.

00:13:05.396 --> 00:13:09.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So it would take real faith on their part

00:13:09.525 --> 00:13:14.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to leave their house, their business,

00:13:14.155 --> 00:13:19.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
close friends and relatives
who wanted to remain in Babylon

00:13:19.160 --> 00:13:24.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and go to Jerusalem
—a city with none of the glitz of Babylon,

00:13:24.165 --> 00:13:28.252 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a city that most of them had never seen.

00:13:28.252 --> 00:13:32.257 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That would take real faith.

00:13:32.257 --> 00:13:36.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the returning Jews
got off to a great start.

00:13:36.052 --> 00:13:40.223 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They constructed
the foundation of the temple,

00:13:40.223 --> 00:13:43.017 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but then they ran into problems.

00:13:43.017 --> 00:13:45.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There was danger.

00:13:45.353 --> 00:13:47.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So how would they show that Jehovah

00:13:47.939 --> 00:13:50.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
comes first in the face of danger?

00:13:50.525 --> 00:13:54.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, they keep on building the temple
in spite of the danger.

00:13:54.362 --> 00:13:56.948 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what do they do?

00:13:56.948 --> 00:14:01.619 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, they got scared,
and they talked themselves

00:14:01.619 --> 00:14:04.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
into believing that it mustn’t be
Jehovah’s will

00:14:04.414 --> 00:14:06.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for them to build the temple.

00:14:06.541 --> 00:14:08.543 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why not?

00:14:08.543 --> 00:14:10.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because it was hard.

00:14:10.545 --> 00:14:14.299 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So they started
looking after themselves,

00:14:14.299 --> 00:14:16.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
looking after their own interests.

00:14:16.760 --> 00:14:20.388 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now remember, Jerusalem was in ruins.

00:14:20.388 --> 00:14:23.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It wasn’t going to be easy
to start a business,

00:14:23.850 --> 00:14:28.313 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
plant crops, and build a house
in a ruined city.

00:14:28.313 --> 00:14:31.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But they didn’t say,
“Oh, this is hard;

00:14:31.483 --> 00:14:33.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so it mustn’t be Jehovah’s will

00:14:33.568 --> 00:14:35.654 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for me to feed my family.”

00:14:35.654 --> 00:14:38.323 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They found a way to feed their family.

00:14:38.323 --> 00:14:41.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, they should’ve had
the same determination

00:14:41.243 --> 00:14:43.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when it came to Jehovah’s worship

00:14:43.287 --> 00:14:47.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because Jehovah has to come first.

00:14:47.082 --> 00:14:50.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, these were good people.

00:14:50.085 --> 00:14:52.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They had had enough faith to leave Babylon

00:14:52.671 --> 00:14:55.299 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and return to Jerusalem in the first place.

00:14:55.299 --> 00:14:58.427 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But that first love had cooled off.

00:14:58.427 --> 00:15:01.180 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, let’s see how Jehovah felt about that.

00:15:01.180 --> 00:15:04.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn to Haggai chapter 1,

00:15:04.391 --> 00:15:06.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we’re going to read
a few verses at Haggai,

00:15:06.935 --> 00:15:08.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so keep your Bibles open there, please.

00:15:08.937 --> 00:15:11.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re going to turn to Haggai chapter 1.

00:15:11.607 --> 00:15:15.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And first of all,
we’re going to read verses 2 through 6

00:15:15.194 --> 00:15:17.196 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to see how Jehovah felt

00:15:17.196 --> 00:15:20.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about this choice
that the Jews had made,

00:15:20.658 --> 00:15:25.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
putting themselves ahead
of his worship in spite of danger.

00:15:26.580 --> 00:15:30.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘This is what Jehovah of armies says,

00:15:30.209 --> 00:15:34.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“These people say,
‘The time has not yet come

00:15:34.421 --> 00:15:37.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for the house of Jehovah to be built.’”’

00:15:37.174 --> 00:15:40.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And the word of Jehovah again
came through Haggai the prophet,

00:15:40.511 --> 00:15:43.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“saying: ‘Is it the time

00:15:43.097 --> 00:15:46.016 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘for you to dwell in your paneled houses,

00:15:46.016 --> 00:15:49.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“while this house lies in ruins?’

00:15:49.437 --> 00:15:52.898 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Now this is what Jehovah of armies says,

00:15:52.898 --> 00:15:55.526 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Set your heart on your ways.

00:15:55.526 --> 00:15:59.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘You have sown much seed,
but you harvest little.

00:15:59.530 --> 00:16:02.825 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘You eat, but it is not to satisfaction.

00:16:02.825 --> 00:16:05.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘You drink, but you do not drink your fill.

00:16:05.995 --> 00:16:09.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘You put on clothing, but no one gets warm.

00:16:09.832 --> 00:16:13.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘The one who hires himself out

00:16:13.002 --> 00:16:17.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
puts his wages in a bag full of holes.’”

00:16:17.215 --> 00:16:20.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, do you think Jehovah
didn’t want them

00:16:20.009 --> 00:16:23.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to build a house or feed their family?

00:16:23.638 --> 00:16:25.640 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of course not.

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:29.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But Jehovah’s worship has to come first.

00:16:29.310 --> 00:16:33.106 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s what exclusive devotion
is all about.

00:16:33.106 --> 00:16:35.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what else
do we learn from these verses?

00:16:35.984 --> 00:16:37.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What’s Jehovah telling the people?

00:16:37.986 --> 00:16:39.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s saying: ‘Look at you.

00:16:39.570 --> 00:16:41.864 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘You work and work and work.

00:16:41.864 --> 00:16:43.866 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘You’re not getting anywhere.

00:16:43.866 --> 00:16:48.872 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’re aren’t getting rich,
and you aren’t even making ends meet.’

00:16:48.872 --> 00:16:50.999 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why not?

00:16:50.999 --> 00:16:54.252 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They didn’t have the blessing of Jehovah.

00:16:54.252 --> 00:16:58.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is the blessing of Jehovah
 that makes one rich.”

00:16:59.424 --> 00:17:02.844 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, one of the scenes
from our dramatic Bible reading

00:17:02.844 --> 00:17:04.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
illustrates this point very well.

00:17:04.888 --> 00:17:06.723 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s remind ourselves.

00:17:06.723 --> 00:17:08.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s have a look.

00:17:09.309 --> 00:17:12.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah compares the results
of the Jews’ self-centered efforts

00:17:12.145 --> 00:17:14.648 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to those of a hired worker who puts

00:17:14.648 --> 00:17:16.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his wages into a moth-eaten sack.

00:17:18.235 --> 00:17:21.613 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because the Jews
are neglecting the house of Jehovah,

00:17:21.613 --> 00:17:23.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he holds back his blessing.

00:17:23.990 --> 00:17:26.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The results of the Jews’ labor are limited,

00:17:26.785 --> 00:17:29.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and their lives lack joy.

00:17:29.329 --> 00:17:32.999 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Evidently, some try to fill that void

00:17:32.999 --> 00:17:36.086 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by beautifying their own homes.

00:17:36.086 --> 00:17:40.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But <i>material</i> things
cannot satisfy spiritual needs.

00:17:40.549 --> 00:17:43.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can we see the warning here for us?

00:17:43.760 --> 00:17:46.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s not wrong to enjoy nice things.

00:17:46.555 --> 00:17:48.432 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But material things

00:17:48.432 --> 00:17:51.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
cannot bring us true and lasting joy,

00:17:51.977 --> 00:17:56.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
especially if we neglect
Jehovah’s work to obtain them.

00:17:58.734 --> 00:18:01.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, there’s nothing wrong
with buying new things.

00:18:01.778 --> 00:18:05.073 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I don’t think many of us
still have a black-and-white TV.

00:18:05.073 --> 00:18:09.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The point is, Jehovah must come first.

00:18:09.244 --> 00:18:13.040 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Remember, the Jews
were facing stiff opposition.

00:18:13.040 --> 00:18:15.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There was danger.

00:18:15.042 --> 00:18:19.338 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So I want you to notice a little detail
as we read Haggai 1:7, 8.

00:18:19.338 --> 00:18:21.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I told you to keep your Bibles open.

00:18:21.715 --> 00:18:26.428 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I didn’t, but I’ve got it again
—Haggai 1:7, 8.

00:18:26.428 --> 00:18:30.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, notice, the Jews are in danger.

00:18:30.140 --> 00:18:35.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There are opposers,
but we’re looking for a little detail

00:18:35.145 --> 00:18:39.775 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that should have reassured
the Jews in verses 7 and 8:

00:18:40.943 --> 00:18:45.948 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“This is what Jehovah of armies says,

00:18:45.948 --> 00:18:48.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Set your heart on your ways.

00:18:48.617 --> 00:18:51.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘Go up to the mountain and bring in lumber.

00:18:51.620 --> 00:18:56.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘And build the house,
so that I may take pleasure in it

00:18:56.042 --> 00:18:59.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I may be a glorified,’ Jehovah says.”

00:18:59.920 --> 00:19:04.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you see it—“Jehovah of armies”?

00:19:04.634 --> 00:19:07.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, that expression
is repeated over and over again

00:19:07.511 --> 00:19:11.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the book of Haggai,
and it should have reassured the Jews

00:19:11.599 --> 00:19:13.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that their enemies were nothing

00:19:13.935 --> 00:19:17.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in comparison with Jehovah
and his armies.

00:19:17.855 --> 00:19:22.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Jehovah telling the Jews:
‘Go ahead.

00:19:22.151 --> 00:19:25.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Build the temple. I have your back.’

00:19:27.782 --> 00:19:32.370 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Find your “greatest joy” in Jehovah.

00:19:32.370 --> 00:19:35.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s really the theme
that we’re talking about today.

00:19:35.665 --> 00:19:37.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s talk about it.

00:19:37.875 --> 00:19:42.338 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And let’s talk about some aspects
of this very important theme.

00:19:42.338 --> 00:19:45.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First of all, we’ll talk
about our relationship with Jehovah.

00:19:45.258 --> 00:19:47.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s so important.

00:19:47.260 --> 00:19:50.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the introduction to this talk,
we mentioned David.

00:19:50.638 --> 00:19:54.517 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had a lot of problems,
maybe more than most of us.

00:19:54.517 --> 00:19:57.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And yet, he never lost his joy.

00:19:57.645 --> 00:20:01.941 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He found joy
in his relationship with Jehovah.

00:20:01.941 --> 00:20:06.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, his physical living conditions
weren’t always the best.

00:20:06.821 --> 00:20:11.284 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When King Saul was alive,
David was on the run most of the time.

00:20:11.284 --> 00:20:13.286 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where did he sleep?

00:20:13.286 --> 00:20:17.332 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In a cave,
in a place “difficult to approach,”

00:20:17.332 --> 00:20:19.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
just anywhere that was safe.

00:20:19.334 --> 00:20:23.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then at times David
and his men ran low on food.

00:20:23.505 --> 00:20:25.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sometimes they ran out of food.

00:20:25.799 --> 00:20:27.801 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you know the feeling?

00:20:27.801 --> 00:20:31.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Have you been low on food
during this pandemic?

00:20:31.680 --> 00:20:35.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
David couldn’t even enjoy
a normal married life

00:20:35.559 --> 00:20:37.644 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because he’d married the daughter of Saul,

00:20:37.644 --> 00:20:40.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but then Saul had given her to another man.

00:20:40.897 --> 00:20:43.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what got him through all that?

00:20:43.483 --> 00:20:46.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His relationship with Jehovah.

00:20:46.194 --> 00:20:49.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah was the constant in his life.

00:20:49.865 --> 00:20:52.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you could just feel
the unbreakable bond

00:20:52.451 --> 00:20:57.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
between Jehovah and David
when you read the 16th Psalm.

00:20:57.039 --> 00:20:59.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, there’s something
very interesting about this Psalm.

00:20:59.416 --> 00:21:01.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn there.

00:21:02.794 --> 00:21:07.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And first of all, we’re just going
to look at verse 1 briefly.

00:21:08.926 --> 00:21:10.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Psalm 16,

00:21:10.928 --> 00:21:15.933 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and notice in verse 1
the situation that David is in.

00:21:15.933 --> 00:21:20.938 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He is in need of protection.

00:21:20.938 --> 00:21:25.943 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In some unstated way,
David is in danger.

00:21:25.943 --> 00:21:28.779 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But you know what’s interesting
about this Psalm?

00:21:28.779 --> 00:21:31.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For the rest of it,
he doesn’t dwell on his problems.

00:21:31.991 --> 00:21:36.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He dwells on the way
Jehovah is helping him with his problems.

00:21:36.412 --> 00:21:40.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Notice verse 8, David says:

00:21:40.749 --> 00:21:45.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I keep Jehovah before me constantly.

00:21:45.379 --> 00:21:50.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because he is at my right hand,
I will never be shaken.”

00:21:51.469 --> 00:21:53.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So with his eyes of faith,

00:21:53.554 --> 00:21:58.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
David could see
Jehovah beside him, protecting him.

00:21:58.309 --> 00:22:01.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, if we can have that vision,
we’re not going to be afraid

00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:04.148 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of anything or anyone, are we?

00:22:04.148 --> 00:22:07.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, find your “greatest joy” in Jehovah?

00:22:07.735 --> 00:22:09.862 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here is a man who is in need of protection.

00:22:09.862 --> 00:22:11.864 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here is a man who feels he’s in danger.

00:22:11.864 --> 00:22:13.866 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Notice verse 9:

00:22:13.866 --> 00:22:18.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“So my heart rejoices,
my whole being is joyful.

00:22:18.871 --> 00:22:21.958 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I reside in security.”

00:22:21.958 --> 00:22:25.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s in danger in some way,
and yet he feels safe.

00:22:25.169 --> 00:22:27.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He feels secure.

00:22:27.171 --> 00:22:29.006 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then notice verse 10.

00:22:29.006 --> 00:22:32.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Usually we apply verse 10
to the resurrection of Jesus.

00:22:32.969 --> 00:22:35.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But think of it from David’s perspective:

00:22:35.638 --> 00:22:39.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For you will not leave me in the Grave.”

00:22:39.475 --> 00:22:43.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
David knew that even if somehow
he were to die,

00:22:43.688 --> 00:22:46.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah would not leave him in the Grave.

00:22:46.357 --> 00:22:48.401 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He would resurrect him.

00:22:48.401 --> 00:22:51.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the end of verse 11,
a beautiful expression:

00:22:51.529 --> 00:22:56.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In your presence is abundant joy.”

00:22:58.578 --> 00:23:00.747 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you notice the expressions

00:23:00.747 --> 00:23:04.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“my heart rejoices,”
“my whole being is joyful,”

00:23:04.250 --> 00:23:08.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in your presence is abundant joy”?

00:23:08.505 --> 00:23:11.674 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
David’s life wasn’t always easy,

00:23:11.674 --> 00:23:15.387 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but feeling that he was
in the presence of Jehovah

00:23:15.387 --> 00:23:17.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—feeling the support of Jehovah—

00:23:17.722 --> 00:23:22.727 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
helped him to get through it
and to get through it with joy.

00:23:22.727 --> 00:23:25.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, your life isn’t always easy.

00:23:25.897 --> 00:23:28.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m sure you’ve had many

00:23:28.024 --> 00:23:30.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
anxious moments during this pandemic.

00:23:30.777 --> 00:23:35.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But then, you turned away from your problems,

00:23:35.407 --> 00:23:39.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you focused on Jehovah God, and you reset.

00:23:39.953 --> 00:23:43.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your joy returned.

00:23:43.039 --> 00:23:47.461 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How many reasons for joy can you think of?

00:23:47.461 --> 00:23:49.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The song says they’re “abundant.”

00:23:49.880 --> 00:23:52.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s think of a few.

00:23:52.049 --> 00:23:54.843 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s one: Jesus said:

00:23:54.843 --> 00:23:59.848 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“No man [no man] can come to me

00:23:59.848 --> 00:24:02.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
unless the Father . . . draws him.”

00:24:02.976 --> 00:24:04.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, think what that means.

00:24:04.978 --> 00:24:09.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah saw something in you that he loves.

00:24:09.316 --> 00:24:11.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He looked down, and he said:

00:24:11.693 --> 00:24:15.697 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I want that person in the new world.”

00:24:15.697 --> 00:24:19.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t try to argue with Jehovah.

00:24:19.117 --> 00:24:21.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t say: “You made a mistake.

00:24:21.495 --> 00:24:22.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You don’t mean me.

00:24:22.704 --> 00:24:24.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“You must mean the fellow next to me.

00:24:24.414 --> 00:24:27.000 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But me?
I’m not worth it.”

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:32.005 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah drew <i>you</i> to the truth.

00:24:32.005 --> 00:24:36.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Accept it.
Accept it.

00:24:36.760 --> 00:24:39.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God loves you.

00:24:39.763 --> 00:24:43.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now that is a reason for joy.

00:24:43.642 --> 00:24:47.938 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Another reason for joy
is that Jehovah answers our prayers.

00:24:47.938 --> 00:24:51.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s always available,
always ready to listen.

00:24:51.483 --> 00:24:54.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We can pray
in any language at any time.

00:24:54.778 --> 00:24:57.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah won’t always do
what we ask him to do,

00:24:57.865 --> 00:25:01.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but he will always listen.

00:25:01.368 --> 00:25:05.372 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We find joy in Jehovah’s service
because he’s reasonable

00:25:05.372 --> 00:25:07.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in what he expects of us.

00:25:07.500 --> 00:25:10.252 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You come home after a long day’s work;

00:25:10.252 --> 00:25:14.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you’re exhausted, worn out, stressed out.

00:25:14.340 --> 00:25:19.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You come home from field service
or from the meeting; you’re refreshed.

00:25:19.345 --> 00:25:22.598 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is reasonable.

00:25:22.598 --> 00:25:24.684 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re also confident that Jehovah

00:25:24.684 --> 00:25:26.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will provide our food and clothing

00:25:26.936 --> 00:25:29.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no matter how dire the situation gets.

00:25:29.397 --> 00:25:32.817 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what he provides
might not always be fancy,

00:25:32.817 --> 00:25:34.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but it’ll always be enough.

00:25:34.986 --> 00:25:38.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’ll always be adequate to get us through.

00:25:38.030 --> 00:25:41.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we should always be grateful
for anything Jehovah provides,

00:25:41.659 --> 00:25:44.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no matter how simple it might be.

00:25:44.871 --> 00:25:47.790 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A researcher once drew a distinction

00:25:47.790 --> 00:25:50.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
between Jehovah’s Witnesses
and some others

00:25:50.710 --> 00:25:54.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who were in concentration camps
in Nazi Germany.

00:25:54.380 --> 00:25:58.635 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A non-Witness might say:
“Where are the gods?

00:25:58.635 --> 00:26:02.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All I have to eat
is this miserable piece of bread.”

00:26:02.555 --> 00:26:05.934 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A Witness in the same camp

00:26:05.934 --> 00:26:09.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
might say: “Oh, Jehovah, thank you.

00:26:09.854 --> 00:26:12.482 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I have a piece of bread to eat.

00:26:12.482 --> 00:26:15.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I can eat and regain my strength

00:26:15.777 --> 00:26:18.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and live just a little longer to serve you.

00:26:18.238 --> 00:26:23.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And maybe I’ll be able to share
some of my bread with someone else.”

00:26:23.243 --> 00:26:28.248 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The conclusion of the researcher:
Both received the piece of bread.

00:26:28.248 --> 00:26:31.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it was all in the point of view.

00:26:31.001 --> 00:26:34.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Witness had a spiritual point of view,

00:26:34.045 --> 00:26:36.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the Witness was grateful

00:26:36.756 --> 00:26:41.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for even a simple provision
that Jehovah had made.

00:26:41.720 --> 00:26:43.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, during this pandemic,

00:26:43.722 --> 00:26:46.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it could be that your menu
has been greatly simplified.

00:26:46.850 --> 00:26:50.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe you haven’t been able to eat
the way you would normally eat.

00:26:50.770 --> 00:26:54.274 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you had just pasta or rice to eat,

00:26:54.274 --> 00:26:56.651 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you didn’t say: “Look at this.

00:26:56.651 --> 00:27:00.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All I have to eat is pasta.
All I have to eat is rice.”

00:27:00.781 --> 00:27:05.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You thanked Jehovah
for the rice or for the pasta.

00:27:05.285 --> 00:27:07.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You were grateful for the provisions.

00:27:07.537 --> 00:27:10.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you realized
that no matter how simple,

00:27:10.415 --> 00:27:14.628 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
these provisions came from Jehovah.

00:27:14.628 --> 00:27:19.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah has also given us
a loving spiritual family.

00:27:19.091 --> 00:27:22.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I think many of us
have come to the conclusion

00:27:22.261 --> 00:27:25.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we never really understood

00:27:25.097 --> 00:27:30.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what a loving spiritual family we have
until this pandemic.

00:27:30.102 --> 00:27:33.522 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A young married couple were both afflicted

00:27:33.522 --> 00:27:36.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the coronavirus—both of them.

00:27:36.608 --> 00:27:37.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, how would they eat?

00:27:37.985 --> 00:27:41.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They couldn’t go out shopping,
and they couldn’t see anyone.

00:27:41.530 --> 00:27:43.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The brother said,

00:27:43.699 --> 00:27:46.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We had groceries at the door constantly.”

00:27:46.952 --> 00:27:51.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The wife says,
“I felt I had Jehovah’s

00:27:51.165 --> 00:27:56.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and everyone else’s arms
wrapped around me.”

00:27:56.170 --> 00:28:01.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Social distancing
doesn’t apply to Jehovah.

00:28:01.175 --> 00:28:05.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He can wrap his arms around anyone.

00:28:05.054 --> 00:28:07.723 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many of our brothers have been reconnecting

00:28:07.723 --> 00:28:11.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with long-lost return visits
and unbelieving family members

00:28:11.393 --> 00:28:13.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and starting Bible studies with them.

00:28:13.771 --> 00:28:17.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And as you probably know,
meeting attendance has increased,

00:28:17.692 --> 00:28:20.152 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and inactive and disfellowshipped persons

00:28:20.152 --> 00:28:23.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are also trying to draw close to Jehovah.

00:28:23.030 --> 00:28:25.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One disfellowshipped person said,

00:28:25.116 --> 00:28:27.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I view this

00:28:27.201 --> 00:28:31.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as one last warning from Jehovah.”

00:28:31.497 --> 00:28:36.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, just a word to any
who may be listening

00:28:36.085 --> 00:28:39.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who are no longer serving Jehovah.

00:28:39.505 --> 00:28:42.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What are you waiting for?

00:28:42.049 --> 00:28:44.302 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God loves you.

00:28:44.302 --> 00:28:46.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God wants you to return.

00:28:46.596 --> 00:28:50.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He wants to put his arms
around you once more.

00:28:50.183 --> 00:28:55.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So please, take advantage
of the invitation, and come back.

00:28:55.146 --> 00:28:58.066 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And please, don’t give in to the idea,

00:28:58.066 --> 00:29:01.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Well, I’ve done nothing up to now,
and now there’s been a pandemic,

00:29:01.361 --> 00:29:03.363 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘and if I come back to the truth,

00:29:03.363 --> 00:29:05.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
well, Jehovah is not going to accept me.’

00:29:05.740 --> 00:29:07.825 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Read your Bible.

00:29:07.825 --> 00:29:09.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ll find that in many cases,

00:29:09.953 --> 00:29:13.581 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it was a disaster of some sort
that caused people

00:29:13.581 --> 00:29:16.251 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to come to their senses
and return to Jehovah,

00:29:16.251 --> 00:29:19.420 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Jehovah lovingly accepted them.

00:29:19.420 --> 00:29:23.007 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think of Manasseh as an example.

00:29:23.007 --> 00:29:27.011 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many have commented
that they’ve actually drawn closer

00:29:27.011 --> 00:29:29.848 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to their brothers and sisters
during this pandemic.

00:29:29.848 --> 00:29:32.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Many, many say,

00:29:32.183 --> 00:29:36.438 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I feel more cared for than ever.”

00:29:36.438 --> 00:29:40.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We find joy in our relationship

00:29:40.025 --> 00:29:43.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with Jehovah
and with our brothers.

00:29:43.445 --> 00:29:46.281 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, we were talking about David.

00:29:46.281 --> 00:29:48.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said in Psalm 16

00:29:48.491 --> 00:29:52.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that there “is abundant joy” in Jehovah.

00:29:52.287 --> 00:29:54.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what was his joy based on?

00:29:54.414 --> 00:29:56.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It wasn’t based on his privileges

00:29:56.917 --> 00:30:00.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—David didn’t become king for years—

00:30:00.170 --> 00:30:03.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but it was on his relationship with Jehovah.

00:30:03.548 --> 00:30:06.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So this is a good example for us.

00:30:06.009 --> 00:30:08.929 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It may be that there is a privilege

00:30:08.929 --> 00:30:11.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you’ve been expecting
that seems a long time coming.

00:30:11.098 --> 00:30:13.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What do you do in the meantime?

00:30:13.350 --> 00:30:16.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Keep working
on your relationship with Jehovah.

00:30:16.228 --> 00:30:18.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Keep strengthening that relationship.

00:30:18.647 --> 00:30:22.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’ll be the best investment
you’ve ever made.

00:30:22.693 --> 00:30:27.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And don’t forget
the greatest privilege any of us can have

00:30:27.239 --> 00:30:29.992 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is to bear the name of Jehovah,

00:30:29.992 --> 00:30:33.453 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to be called one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:30:33.453 --> 00:30:37.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we’re part of a family
of brothers and sisters

00:30:37.541 --> 00:30:42.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who love us and who would
even risk their lives for us.

00:30:42.045 --> 00:30:45.299 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So we’ve discussed finding joy

00:30:45.299 --> 00:30:48.302 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in our relationship with Jehovah.

00:30:48.302 --> 00:30:50.304 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s consider a second aspect,

00:30:50.304 --> 00:30:54.433 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that is finding joy in the Bible,

00:30:54.433 --> 00:30:58.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
finding joy in God’s written Word.

00:30:58.812 --> 00:31:01.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We get to know Jehovah best

00:31:01.649 --> 00:31:05.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by reading his Word and meditating on it.

00:31:05.236 --> 00:31:08.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, in recent times,
the congregation Bible reading

00:31:08.322 --> 00:31:11.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has been shortened,
and there’s a good reason for that.

00:31:11.617 --> 00:31:14.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s not so we can get
our Bible reading over with

00:31:14.620 --> 00:31:16.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and get on to other things.

00:31:16.622 --> 00:31:20.167 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s so that we will take our time,
slow down,

00:31:20.167 --> 00:31:22.336 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
meditate on what we’re reading.

00:31:22.336 --> 00:31:25.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Chew it up; digest it thoroughly.

00:31:25.047 --> 00:31:30.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Jehovah talking to you and to me,
sharing his thoughts with us.

00:31:30.052 --> 00:31:33.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is amazing,
and we need to appreciate it.

00:31:33.764 --> 00:31:38.019 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, one way
that we can enjoy our Bible reading

00:31:38.019 --> 00:31:41.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is to make the connection
between what we’re reading now

00:31:41.314 --> 00:31:45.276 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and what we’ve read in the past
and see how they match up.

00:31:45.276 --> 00:31:48.029 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s take an example—just a short one.

00:31:48.029 --> 00:31:53.034 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Turn to Numbers chapter 12

00:31:53.034 --> 00:31:58.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Numbers 12:1, 2.

00:31:58.039 --> 00:32:02.251 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I think the setting
is pretty self-explanatory.

00:32:02.251 --> 00:32:07.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So Numbers 12:1, 2:

00:32:07.256 --> 00:32:12.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Now Miriam and Aaron
began to speak against Moses

00:32:12.262 --> 00:32:15.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“because of the Cushite wife he had married,

00:32:15.431 --> 00:32:18.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for he had taken a Cushite wife.

00:32:18.184 --> 00:32:23.064 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“They were saying: ‘Is it only by Moses
that Jehovah has spoken?

00:32:23.064 --> 00:32:26.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Has he not also spoken through us?’”

00:32:26.568 --> 00:32:29.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what was their argument?

00:32:29.320 --> 00:32:33.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Basically, in plain English,
their argument was that Moses

00:32:33.950 --> 00:32:38.955 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was hogging the limelight,
that he wanted to be the center of attention.

00:32:38.955 --> 00:32:41.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, is that true?

00:32:41.624 --> 00:32:45.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the previous chapter
—chapter 11—

00:32:45.170 --> 00:32:47.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what do we read?

00:32:47.172 --> 00:32:51.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Moses willingly shares his authority

00:32:51.593 --> 00:32:55.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with 70 of the men of the elders of Israel.

00:32:55.764 --> 00:32:58.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So there was no serious question

00:32:58.266 --> 00:33:01.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about Moses wanting to have the limelight.

00:33:01.561 --> 00:33:04.773 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Moses was a humble man.

00:33:04.773 --> 00:33:09.069 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, this is Numbers chapter 12.

00:33:09.069 --> 00:33:11.071 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Aaron

00:33:11.071 --> 00:33:14.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
questioning Moses’ authority.

00:33:14.700 --> 00:33:18.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we can learn a little bit more about this

00:33:18.245 --> 00:33:20.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from something that is tucked far away

00:33:20.414 --> 00:33:22.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the book of Deuteronomy.

00:33:22.624 --> 00:33:25.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn to Deuteronomy chapter 9,

00:33:25.961 --> 00:33:28.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we’re going to see
if we can learn something

00:33:28.171 --> 00:33:31.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about Aaron and why Aaron’s attitude

00:33:31.717 --> 00:33:33.886 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was so shocking

00:33:33.886 --> 00:33:38.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Deuteronomy 9:20.

00:33:38.891 --> 00:33:42.811 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is a revelation.

00:33:42.811 --> 00:33:46.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is Moses
in the very last month of his life,

00:33:46.732 --> 00:33:49.359 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
talking to the Israelites,
and he says:

00:33:49.359 --> 00:33:53.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah was so angry with Aaron

00:33:53.739 --> 00:33:56.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that he was ready to annihilate him,

00:33:56.700 --> 00:34:00.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but I made supplication for Aaron.”

00:34:00.996 --> 00:34:05.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Aaron owed his life to Moses.

00:34:05.125 --> 00:34:09.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And yet, he dares
to question Moses’ leadership

00:34:09.755 --> 00:34:12.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the nation of Israel.

00:34:12.091 --> 00:34:14.635 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That is really shocking.

00:34:14.635 --> 00:34:17.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now,
what does this teach you about Moses?

00:34:17.721 --> 00:34:20.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He is a very humble man,

00:34:20.558 --> 00:34:23.436 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he’s not quick to take credit for things.

00:34:23.436 --> 00:34:25.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, why do we say that?

00:34:25.688 --> 00:34:30.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Moses wrote the book of Exodus
and the story of the golden calf,

00:34:30.693 --> 00:34:34.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he never mentioned that Jehovah
wanted to annihilate Aaron

00:34:34.989 --> 00:34:38.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for his part in the golden-calf incident.

00:34:38.242 --> 00:34:40.411 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Aaron was still alive,

00:34:40.411 --> 00:34:44.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Moses spared Aaron that indignity.

00:34:44.707 --> 00:34:49.295 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s only after Aaron’s death

00:34:49.295 --> 00:34:53.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and in the very last month
of Moses’ life that we learn about it.

00:34:53.549 --> 00:34:58.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Doesn’t that tell you something
about how kind and humble Moses was?

00:34:58.554 --> 00:35:02.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So this is just to illustrate the fact

00:35:02.308 --> 00:35:06.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that if we try to take one point
that we’ve learned in the past

00:35:06.979 --> 00:35:09.023 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and connect it up
with what we’re reading now,

00:35:09.023 --> 00:35:12.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it will often help
the Bible reading to come alive.

00:35:12.527 --> 00:35:14.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now let’s consider some of the things

00:35:14.570 --> 00:35:17.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that God’s Word has done for us.

00:35:17.532 --> 00:35:21.369 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you remember what it was like
before you came into the truth?

00:35:21.369 --> 00:35:25.582 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A favorite relative of yours
who was happily married

00:35:25.582 --> 00:35:28.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
lost her husband in death.

00:35:28.334 --> 00:35:31.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the funeral, a priest told her

00:35:31.796 --> 00:35:34.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that her husband was in purgatory.

00:35:34.215 --> 00:35:36.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And unless the widow paid up,

00:35:36.217 --> 00:35:39.053 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he was going to stay there for a long time.

00:35:39.053 --> 00:35:41.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
She’d just lost her husband.

00:35:41.514 --> 00:35:43.850 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How comforting was that?

00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:47.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But then you started studying the Bible.

00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:52.484 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You came to Romans 6:7:

00:35:52.484 --> 00:35:57.489 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The one who has died
has been acquitted from his sin.”

00:35:57.489 --> 00:36:00.075 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Acquitted from his sin”

00:36:00.075 --> 00:36:03.286 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and your Bible teacher
explained what that means.

00:36:03.286 --> 00:36:07.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It means that when you die,
the debt is paid.

00:36:07.541 --> 00:36:10.585 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You don’t go on paying after death.

00:36:10.585 --> 00:36:15.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You don’t suffer in hell,
and you don’t suffer in purgatory.

00:36:15.215 --> 00:36:19.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That one Bible verse
could completely change your view

00:36:19.052 --> 00:36:22.347 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of what happens at death.

00:36:22.347 --> 00:36:25.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On the other hand,
maybe you grew up in a family

00:36:25.308 --> 00:36:28.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where evolution was the order of the day

00:36:28.854 --> 00:36:33.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—so no hope, no hope for the future.

00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:36.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This life is all there is.

00:36:36.445 --> 00:36:38.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then you came to learn

00:36:38.989 --> 00:36:42.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you have a heavenly Father
who loves you very much

00:36:42.201 --> 00:36:45.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and who wants to give you
a future and a hope.

00:36:45.245 --> 00:36:49.458 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a joy it was to discover Jehovah!

00:36:49.458 --> 00:36:51.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of us grew up in a family

00:36:51.460 --> 00:36:53.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where the parents didn’t get along so well.

00:36:53.796 --> 00:36:56.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We couldn’t point to them and say,

00:36:56.256 --> 00:36:59.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Now that is how
a man should treat his wife,”

00:36:59.093 --> 00:37:02.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or “That is how a woman
should treat her husband.”

00:37:02.596 --> 00:37:05.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They just didn’t get along.

00:37:05.140 --> 00:37:07.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We needed Jehovah; we needed the Bible;

00:37:07.393 --> 00:37:09.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we needed Jehovah’s organization

00:37:09.561 --> 00:37:13.315 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to teach us how to have a happy family life.

00:37:13.315 --> 00:37:15.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s more.

00:37:15.734 --> 00:37:18.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Recently a clergyman
was asked by a journalist

00:37:18.821 --> 00:37:22.783 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
why pandemics like the coronavirus occur.

00:37:22.783 --> 00:37:24.827 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the clergyman answered,

00:37:24.827 --> 00:37:28.372 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Well, suffering is part of life.”

00:37:28.372 --> 00:37:31.208 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That didn’t answer the question.

00:37:31.208 --> 00:37:34.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The journalist wasn’t asking, ‘Do we suffer?’

00:37:34.670 --> 00:37:36.839 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The journalist knew that we suffer.

00:37:36.839 --> 00:37:40.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The journalist wanted to know why we suffer.

00:37:40.384 --> 00:37:42.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He didn’t get an answer.

00:37:42.678 --> 00:37:45.056 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A professor of New Testament theology

00:37:45.056 --> 00:37:48.809 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was asked the same question,
Why do we suffer?

00:37:48.809 --> 00:37:51.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you know what he said?

00:37:51.020 --> 00:37:53.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Everybody suffers.

00:37:53.189 --> 00:37:55.191 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God suffers.”

00:37:55.191 --> 00:37:57.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What kind of an answer is that?

00:37:57.944 --> 00:38:00.947 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How happy we are to have the answers

00:38:00.947 --> 00:38:03.741 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to those questions from the Bible.

00:38:03.741 --> 00:38:07.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, speaking about God’s written Word,

00:38:07.537 --> 00:38:12.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
since 1966, Jehovah’s organization
has made the Bible come alive

00:38:12.542 --> 00:38:16.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the most outstanding way
through the Bible dramas.

00:38:16.796 --> 00:38:19.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It really has made the Bible come alive,
hasn’t it?

00:38:19.924 --> 00:38:23.094 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s helped us to visualize
what life was like in Bible times,

00:38:23.094 --> 00:38:26.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we’ve come to realize
that people living in Bible times

00:38:26.431 --> 00:38:30.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
weren’t really so very different
from people who are living today.

00:38:30.226 --> 00:38:35.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s review a few scenes
and see what lessons we can glean.

00:38:35.231 --> 00:38:37.233 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Have a look.

00:38:44.449 --> 00:38:45.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham!

00:38:46.993 --> 00:38:48.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We had a visitor last night.

00:38:50.955 --> 00:38:52.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was your wife,

00:38:55.877 --> 00:38:57.879 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or should I say your former wife.

00:38:59.214 --> 00:39:00.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham,

00:39:00.382 --> 00:39:03.468 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
don’t you care how you’ve hurt your innocent mate?

00:39:03.468 --> 00:39:05.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How can you be so hard-hearted?

00:39:05.470 --> 00:39:07.806 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Look! Moses said if you find something

00:39:07.806 --> 00:39:10.058 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
indecent with your wife, a man must write

00:39:10.058 --> 00:39:12.060 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a certificate of divorce, hand it to her,

00:39:12.060 --> 00:39:13.478 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and dismiss her.

00:39:13.478 --> 00:39:17.399 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If giving me no children isn’t indecent, then what is?

00:39:17.399 --> 00:39:19.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Besides, I’m tired of living with her.

00:39:19.568 --> 00:39:21.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m marrying Gizla today.

00:39:21.194 --> 00:39:22.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Gizla?

00:39:22.821 --> 00:39:24.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That Moabite girl?

00:39:26.199 --> 00:39:28.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I heard you bind yourself with an oath and a curse

00:39:28.702 --> 00:39:30.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not to take a wife from the nations!

00:39:30.537 --> 00:39:33.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God’s Law says: “They will turn your sons away

00:39:33.165 --> 00:39:35.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“from following me to serve other gods;

00:39:35.542 --> 00:39:38.295 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
then Jehovah’s anger will blaze against you”!

00:39:38.295 --> 00:39:40.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who are you to counsel me?

00:39:40.464 --> 00:39:42.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Every man must find his own joy,

00:39:42.591 --> 00:39:44.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and I intend to find mine.

00:39:44.968 --> 00:39:49.473 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham, only Jehovah can give true joy.

00:39:49.473 --> 00:39:50.933 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you really think you can give

00:39:50.933 --> 00:39:52.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
yourself more joy than he can?

00:40:00.150 --> 00:40:02.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What’s the lesson?

00:40:02.361 --> 00:40:07.241 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our “greatest joy” comes
when we obey Jehovah.

00:40:07.241 --> 00:40:10.077 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s look again.

00:40:13.747 --> 00:40:15.124 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come along.

00:40:15.124 --> 00:40:17.751 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>Ana la mitbayen.</i>

00:40:17.751 --> 00:40:19.795 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come back here!

00:40:19.795 --> 00:40:21.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have to listen to me. I’m your father!

00:40:21.547 --> 00:40:23.424 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What’s wrong with your children?

00:40:24.633 --> 00:40:26.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They don’t like coming to the temple.

00:40:26.969 --> 00:40:30.931 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sweetie, why don’t you like it?

00:40:30.931 --> 00:40:32.057 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>Shvok Y-ati!</i>

00:40:33.559 --> 00:40:34.769 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come back here now!

00:40:38.856 --> 00:40:40.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m sorry, my lord.

00:40:40.858 --> 00:40:42.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My wife speaks very little Hebrew.

00:40:44.320 --> 00:40:47.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you not swear never to marry someone

00:40:47.031 --> 00:40:48.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who doesn’t serve Jehovah?

00:40:48.574 --> 00:40:50.076 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Nehemiah, nobody cares.

00:40:51.410 --> 00:40:52.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you not?

00:40:52.995 --> 00:40:54.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes! Yes!

00:40:54.163 --> 00:40:55.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then why have you ignored the command of Jehovah

00:40:55.957 --> 00:40:58.167 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and your own oath?

00:40:58.167 --> 00:40:59.210 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let me go!

00:40:59.210 --> 00:41:01.879 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No wonder your children don’t love Jehovah.

00:41:01.879 --> 00:41:03.005 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Aah!

00:41:03.005 --> 00:41:04.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you imagine that you could succeed

00:41:04.715 --> 00:41:06.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
without Jehovah’s blessing?

00:41:06.592 --> 00:41:08.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I prayed for Jehovah’s blessing!

00:41:08.136 --> 00:41:08.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you?

00:41:08.970 --> 00:41:10.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But you didn’t obey him.

00:41:10.972 --> 00:41:14.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham, how can Jehovah bless something

00:41:14.267 --> 00:41:16.728 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that is against his will?

00:41:20.857 --> 00:41:22.900 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the lesson here?

00:41:22.900 --> 00:41:25.069 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah doesn’t answer prayers

00:41:25.069 --> 00:41:27.655 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that are not in harmony with his will.

00:41:27.655 --> 00:41:29.782 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And again—

00:41:36.623 --> 00:41:38.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What was that all about?

00:41:39.500 --> 00:41:41.377 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham refuses to move into Jerusalem,

00:41:45.548 --> 00:41:47.550 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he wants us to support him.

00:41:47.550 --> 00:41:49.010 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What did you say?

00:41:50.970 --> 00:41:54.057 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I told him Nehemiah is doing Jehovah’s will.

00:41:55.683 --> 00:41:57.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Raham doesn’t understand how happy

00:41:57.686 --> 00:42:01.439 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he could be if-if he would just follow Jehovah’s direction.

00:42:04.234 --> 00:42:07.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So we will move if we are selected?

00:42:09.072 --> 00:42:10.073 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes.

00:42:12.450 --> 00:42:16.830 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’d rather be like Nehemiah than like Raham.

00:42:16.830 --> 00:42:18.373 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You agree?

00:42:18.373 --> 00:42:19.833 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes.

00:42:19.833 --> 00:42:21.835 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Me too.

00:42:24.504 --> 00:42:26.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The lesson?

00:42:26.506 --> 00:42:30.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Happy families follow Jehovah’s direction.

00:42:30.969 --> 00:42:35.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, there are a lot more lessons
to be learned from this drama.

00:42:35.974 --> 00:42:39.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you can discover them
as you review it at home.

00:42:39.770 --> 00:42:44.775 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You guessed it,
we’re releasing the drama today.

00:42:44.775 --> 00:42:47.945 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You can access it following this talk.

00:42:47.945 --> 00:42:51.782 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The chairman will show you how.

00:42:51.782 --> 00:42:56.787 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may applaud.

00:42:56.787 --> 00:43:01.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So we find joy
in our relationship with Jehovah.

00:43:01.500 --> 00:43:04.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We find joy in studying his Word

00:43:04.169 --> 00:43:07.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and discovering beautiful things in his Word.

00:43:07.131 --> 00:43:09.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what about Jehovah’s name?

00:43:09.967 --> 00:43:14.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can we find joy in Jehovah’s name as well?

00:43:14.596 --> 00:43:17.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Particularly in the last few years,

00:43:17.558 --> 00:43:20.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a lot of emphasis has been placed
on Jehovah’s name.

00:43:20.894 --> 00:43:23.480 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At Warwick, in the museum,

00:43:23.480 --> 00:43:27.568 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we even have an exhibit
about the divine name.

00:43:27.568 --> 00:43:29.612 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, why do you suppose that is?

00:43:29.612 --> 00:43:33.490 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why do you think there’s
so much emphasis on God’s name?

00:43:33.490 --> 00:43:36.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, Jehovah loves his name,

00:43:36.702 --> 00:43:40.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he loves those who love his name.

00:43:40.498 --> 00:43:44.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s something we discover
when we read Malachi chapter 3

00:43:47.338 --> 00:43:50.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Malachi chapter 3,

00:43:50.758 --> 00:43:53.803 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and verse 16.

00:43:56.305 --> 00:43:58.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ll give you a moment.

00:43:58.599 --> 00:44:03.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Malachi 3:16:

00:44:05.606 --> 00:44:10.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“At that time those who fear Jehovah
spoke with one another,

00:44:10.611 --> 00:44:12.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“each one with his companion,

00:44:12.989 --> 00:44:16.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and Jehovah
kept paying attention and listening.

00:44:16.784 --> 00:44:19.370 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And a book of remembrance was written

00:44:19.370 --> 00:44:22.415 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“before him for those fearing Jehovah

00:44:22.415 --> 00:44:26.210 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[and notice this] and for those

00:44:26.210 --> 00:44:29.297 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
meditating on his name.”

00:44:29.297 --> 00:44:32.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then, in chapter 4 and verse 2,

00:44:32.300 --> 00:44:36.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah praises those “who honor [His] name.”

00:44:36.888 --> 00:44:39.223 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, let’s go back to this expression

00:44:39.223 --> 00:44:42.185 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“those meditating on his name.”

00:44:42.185 --> 00:44:44.354 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What do you think that means?

00:44:44.354 --> 00:44:48.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Surely it means more than
just accepting that God has a name.

00:44:48.441 --> 00:44:50.819 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We know that.

00:44:50.819 --> 00:44:53.071 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Jews in Malachi’s day,

00:44:53.071 --> 00:44:56.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even the unfaithful ones, knew that.

00:44:56.074 --> 00:45:01.079 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But surely it means meditating
on the meaning of God’s name

00:45:01.079 --> 00:45:03.331 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and meditating on the role

00:45:03.331 --> 00:45:07.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we can have in vindicating his name.

00:45:07.544 --> 00:45:11.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As you know, many scholars
believe that Jehovah’s name

00:45:11.798 --> 00:45:15.302 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
means “He Causes to Become.”

00:45:15.302 --> 00:45:19.389 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah can become
whatever he needs to become,

00:45:19.389 --> 00:45:24.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he can make you become
whatever he needs you to be.

00:45:24.144 --> 00:45:27.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the days of Israel,
what did Jehovah need?

00:45:27.856 --> 00:45:30.192 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Often he needed prophets.

00:45:30.192 --> 00:45:32.319 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where did he get them?

00:45:32.319 --> 00:45:34.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From ordinary people.

00:45:34.321 --> 00:45:36.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He took a very shy young man named Jeremiah

00:45:36.990 --> 00:45:40.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and turned him
into a bold and courageous prophet.

00:45:40.160 --> 00:45:44.706 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he did the same with a farmer named Amos.

00:45:44.706 --> 00:45:49.711 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t tell Jehovah what you can and can’t do.

00:45:49.711 --> 00:45:54.007 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You might be surprised
about what you can do

00:45:54.007 --> 00:45:57.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
if you just put yourself in Jehovah’s hands.

00:45:57.177 --> 00:46:01.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How many in this audience once said:

00:46:01.265 --> 00:46:04.768 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I could never preach from door to door,”

00:46:04.768 --> 00:46:09.690 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I could never pioneer,”
“I could never be a missionary,”

00:46:09.690 --> 00:46:13.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I could never serve
where the need is great”?

00:46:13.902 --> 00:46:17.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, Jehovah knew better.

00:46:17.656 --> 00:46:21.994 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We can trust Jehovah
and what he promises to do.

00:46:21.994 --> 00:46:24.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He will always keep his promises.

00:46:24.330 --> 00:46:26.332 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, when you
go through the Hebrew Scriptures,

00:46:26.332 --> 00:46:29.668 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you find certain expressions
over and over again.

00:46:29.668 --> 00:46:31.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Jews rebel against Jehovah.

00:46:31.837 --> 00:46:35.132 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They do terrible things,
sometimes disgusting things.

00:46:35.132 --> 00:46:38.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you, the reader, are saying:

00:46:38.093 --> 00:46:41.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Jehovah, you really
ought to annihilate these people.

00:46:41.222 --> 00:46:43.432 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s terrible what they’re doing.’

00:46:43.432 --> 00:46:46.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But then Jehovah reconsiders.

00:46:46.977 --> 00:46:49.105 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why?

00:46:49.105 --> 00:46:53.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘For the sake of my promise
that I made to Abraham,’

00:46:53.025 --> 00:46:56.737 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘for the sake of the covenant
that [I] made with [my servant] David,’

00:46:56.737 --> 00:47:00.449 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘for the sake of my name’”

00:47:00.449 --> 00:47:05.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—to Jehovah, a promise is a promise.

00:47:05.246 --> 00:47:08.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He promised Abraham and David

00:47:08.165 --> 00:47:11.502 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he wouldn’t forsake their offspring.

00:47:11.502 --> 00:47:13.504 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he meant what he said.

00:47:13.504 --> 00:47:15.840 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now think what that means.

00:47:15.840 --> 00:47:19.969 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Nothing will make
Jehovah go back on his word.

00:47:19.969 --> 00:47:22.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Jehovah promises
that he’s going to take this earth

00:47:22.638 --> 00:47:26.225 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and turn it into a paradise,
you can take that to the bank.

00:47:26.225 --> 00:47:30.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah will keep his promise.

00:47:30.271 --> 00:47:33.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, how has Jehovah shown
that a promise is a promise

00:47:33.858 --> 00:47:35.860 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during this convention?

00:47:35.860 --> 00:47:37.945 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What did he promise?

00:47:37.945 --> 00:47:41.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“My servants will eat.”

00:47:41.491 --> 00:47:45.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the Governing Body
had to find a way to serve the food.

00:47:45.245 --> 00:47:47.538 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah provided the food.

00:47:47.538 --> 00:47:49.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He provided it in abundance.

00:47:49.707 --> 00:47:51.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we thank him for it.

00:47:51.834 --> 00:47:56.840 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All praise goes to Jehovah
for this convention program.

00:47:56.840 --> 00:48:00.426 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, when we first discovered
that God has a name,

00:48:00.426 --> 00:48:03.096 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it was a turning point for many of us.

00:48:03.096 --> 00:48:06.516 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A circuit overseer was going
from door to door one morning,

00:48:06.516 --> 00:48:09.644 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and at one door,
a teenage boy answered.

00:48:09.644 --> 00:48:12.814 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He announced
that his parents were not at home,

00:48:12.814 --> 00:48:15.066 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the circuit overseer said,

00:48:15.066 --> 00:48:18.528 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Well, just before I leave
I’d like to show you something.”

00:48:18.528 --> 00:48:21.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he showed the boy Jehovah’s name

00:48:21.823 --> 00:48:25.535 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the Bible—Psalm 83:18.

00:48:25.535 --> 00:48:28.872 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The boy took the Bible to have a closer look,

00:48:28.872 --> 00:48:32.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
turned around, went into the house,

00:48:32.042 --> 00:48:37.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and shut the door
—with the circuit overseer’s Bible.

00:48:37.047 --> 00:48:41.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The circuit overseer waited and waited,

00:48:41.927 --> 00:48:44.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he thought he’d lost his Bible.

00:48:44.596 --> 00:48:48.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But then the boy’s mother
came to the door,

00:48:48.141 --> 00:48:50.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and she apologized for pretending
that she wasn’t home.

00:48:50.852 --> 00:48:53.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But she said she had been astonished

00:48:53.897 --> 00:48:56.775 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to learn that God has a name.

00:48:56.775 --> 00:48:59.945 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That led to a good witness.

00:48:59.945 --> 00:49:03.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what else
do we know about God’s name?

00:49:03.615 --> 00:49:08.620 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible says that “the name
of Jehovah is a strong tower.”

00:49:08.620 --> 00:49:12.457 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we’re going to be able
to count on Jehovah

00:49:12.457 --> 00:49:15.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during the attack of Gog of Magog.

00:49:15.919 --> 00:49:20.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Gog attacks,
Jehovah is going to vindicate himself

00:49:20.924 --> 00:49:25.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—He is going to protect His people
for the sake of His name.

00:49:25.888 --> 00:49:29.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that’s another reason
for us to love Jehovah’s name

00:49:29.808 --> 00:49:32.019 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—to rejoice in his name.

00:49:32.019 --> 00:49:37.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because his name is involved,
Jehovah is going to protect his people.

00:49:37.024 --> 00:49:40.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, when we talk
about the attack of Gog and Magog,

00:49:40.611 --> 00:49:42.613 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
does it make you kind of nervous?

00:49:42.613 --> 00:49:45.324 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here are a couple of things to think about.

00:49:45.324 --> 00:49:47.326 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First of all,

00:49:47.326 --> 00:49:51.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
whose idea is it
for Gog to attack when he does?

00:49:51.622 --> 00:49:53.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s find out.

00:49:53.624 --> 00:49:56.585 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ezekiel chapter 38

00:50:01.549 --> 00:50:04.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
(and we’re going to start with verse 4),

00:50:04.593 --> 00:50:07.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ezekiel 38 beginning with verse 4.

00:50:07.888 --> 00:50:10.433 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, this is Jehovah talking

00:50:10.433 --> 00:50:13.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to that coalition of nations

00:50:13.102 --> 00:50:16.272 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
known collectively as Gog.

00:50:16.272 --> 00:50:18.983 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I want you to pay particular attention

00:50:18.983 --> 00:50:22.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the first part of the verse,
that’s verse 4.

00:50:22.445 --> 00:50:25.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah says to Gog:

00:50:25.031 --> 00:50:29.577 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will turn you around

00:50:29.577 --> 00:50:33.623 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and put hooks in your jaws

00:50:33.623 --> 00:50:38.628 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and bring you out with all your army.”

00:50:38.628 --> 00:50:41.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now think about that.

00:50:41.047 --> 00:50:44.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will turn you around.”

00:50:44.300 --> 00:50:48.179 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It sounds like Gog
was headed in the opposite direction,

00:50:48.179 --> 00:50:50.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but then Jehovah turns him around,

00:50:50.390 --> 00:50:53.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and He draws him out to attack.

00:50:53.434 --> 00:50:55.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what does that tell you?

00:50:55.562 --> 00:50:59.691 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The timing of the attack is Jehovah’s.

00:50:59.691 --> 00:51:02.360 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, that doesn’t mean that Gog of Magog

00:51:02.360 --> 00:51:04.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had no intention of attacking God’s people.

00:51:04.529 --> 00:51:07.782 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He was planning to attack at some point.

00:51:07.782 --> 00:51:11.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it’s the timing
of the attack that’s Jehovah’s.

00:51:11.578 --> 00:51:14.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The <i>Pure Worship</i> book
explains it this way—it says:

00:51:14.748 --> 00:51:19.711 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As if putting hooks
in Gog’s jaws and leading him along . . .

00:51:19.711 --> 00:51:23.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“At some point following the destruction
of Babylon the Great,

00:51:23.506 --> 00:51:27.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah may in some way lure the nations

00:51:27.052 --> 00:51:30.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“into carrying out
what is already in their hearts.

00:51:30.722 --> 00:51:34.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah will thus set the stage

00:51:34.851 --> 00:51:37.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the attack that leads to Armageddon.”

00:51:37.771 --> 00:51:40.816 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what are we worried about?

00:51:40.816 --> 00:51:45.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Everything is happening
according to Jehovah’s purpose.

00:51:45.320 --> 00:51:49.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, when we read verses 10-12,

00:51:49.199 --> 00:51:52.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we see what Gog has in mind.

00:51:52.703 --> 00:51:57.124 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ezekiel 38:10-12,

00:51:57.124 --> 00:52:01.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then leave your Bibles open,
because we’ll read one more verse.

00:52:01.503 --> 00:52:04.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verses 10 to 12, it says:

00:52:04.131 --> 00:52:07.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘This is what
the Sovereign Lord Jehovah says:

00:52:07.217 --> 00:52:11.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“In that day thoughts
will come into your heart

00:52:11.722 --> 00:52:14.349 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“[I wonder who put them there?],

00:52:14.349 --> 00:52:17.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“and you will devise an evil plan.

00:52:17.561 --> 00:52:22.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“You I will say: ‘I will invade the land
of unprotected settlements.

00:52:22.065 --> 00:52:24.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“‘I will come against
those living in security,

00:52:24.902 --> 00:52:28.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“‘without disturbance,
all of them living in settlements

00:52:28.030 --> 00:52:31.825 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘“unprotected by walls, bars, or gates.’

00:52:31.825 --> 00:52:36.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It will be to take much spoil and plunder.”’”

00:52:36.246 --> 00:52:39.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But how will it all work out?

00:52:39.333 --> 00:52:41.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 23:

00:52:41.710 --> 00:52:44.922 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“And I [that is, Jehovah, I]

00:52:44.922 --> 00:52:49.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“will certainly magnify myself
and sanctify myself

00:52:49.510 --> 00:52:53.347 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and make myself known
before the eyes of many nations

00:52:53.347 --> 00:52:58.227 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they will have to know
that I am Jehovah.”

00:52:58.227 --> 00:53:00.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what do we learn?

00:53:00.271 --> 00:53:03.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Everything is under control.

00:53:03.899 --> 00:53:05.943 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is no need to panic.

00:53:05.943 --> 00:53:09.655 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Everything is going according to schedule

00:53:09.655 --> 00:53:12.575 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Jehovah’s schedule.

00:53:12.575 --> 00:53:15.161 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So that’s the first thing.

00:53:15.161 --> 00:53:17.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is another thing.

00:53:17.246 --> 00:53:20.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What precedes the attack of Gog and Magog?

00:53:20.499 --> 00:53:23.336 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What did we read in the <i>Pure Worship</i> book?

00:53:23.336 --> 00:53:26.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The destruction of Babylon the Great.

00:53:26.797 --> 00:53:28.883 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, have you ever considered

00:53:28.883 --> 00:53:32.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how that destruction
is going to fortify your faith

00:53:32.386 --> 00:53:34.472 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—is going to strengthen you—

00:53:34.472 --> 00:53:38.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so that you’re able
to endure the attack of Gog of Magog?

00:53:38.059 --> 00:53:40.269 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think about it this way:

00:53:40.269 --> 00:53:43.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What other religious organization

00:53:43.731 --> 00:53:48.736 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
foretells the destruction
of a world empire of false religion?

00:53:48.736 --> 00:53:50.947 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re the only ones,

00:53:50.947 --> 00:53:53.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because the others
are all part of Babylon the Great.

00:53:53.199 --> 00:53:56.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They’re not going to foretell
their destruction in the future.

00:53:56.786 --> 00:53:59.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So the destruction is going to be a surprise

00:53:59.622 --> 00:54:02.625 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to everyone but Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:54:02.625 --> 00:54:06.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And when it occurs,
there’ll be no doubt in your mind

00:54:06.421 --> 00:54:10.216 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you’re on the winning side
—that you’re on Jehovah’s side.

00:54:10.216 --> 00:54:14.846 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some brothers get all upset
over some detail

00:54:14.846 --> 00:54:17.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they don’t think the organization
has the right take on.

00:54:17.974 --> 00:54:20.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It might be the pronunciation of God’s name

00:54:20.894 --> 00:54:23.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or the meaning of that name

00:54:23.104 --> 00:54:25.648 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or the meaning
of a single verse in the Scriptures.

00:54:25.648 --> 00:54:27.150 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They get all upset.

00:54:27.150 --> 00:54:29.569 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They get obsessed over one detail,

00:54:29.569 --> 00:54:33.490 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and it interferes with their worship.

00:54:33.490 --> 00:54:36.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But when Babylon the Great goes down,

00:54:36.409 --> 00:54:40.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will there be any doubt as to which channel

00:54:40.038 --> 00:54:43.750 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah God has been using
all this time to do his will?

00:54:43.750 --> 00:54:48.672 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You will be so glad
that you’re on the winning side.

00:54:48.672 --> 00:54:52.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of course, it is sobering to think

00:54:52.217 --> 00:54:56.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about the final attack
of Gog of Magog on God’s people.

00:54:56.680 --> 00:54:59.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it shouldn’t take away our joy.

00:54:59.224 --> 00:55:03.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Nehemiah 8:10, it says:

00:55:03.311 --> 00:55:07.858 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.”

00:55:07.858 --> 00:55:12.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joy is actually a protection for us.

00:55:12.237 --> 00:55:15.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, did Nehemiah need a stronghold?

00:55:15.657 --> 00:55:17.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You know the answer to that.

00:55:17.826 --> 00:55:20.829 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His life was being threatened.

00:55:20.829 --> 00:55:24.750 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Pagan inhabitants of the land
wanted to kill him,

00:55:24.750 --> 00:55:27.669 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then there were problems
in the congregation.

00:55:27.669 --> 00:55:31.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some of the elders weren’t respecting
Jehovah’s law on marriage,

00:55:31.381 --> 00:55:33.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the Sabbath wasn’t being observed.

00:55:33.634 --> 00:55:35.636 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that was one of the reasons

00:55:35.636 --> 00:55:38.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
why the Jews went into captivity
in the first place.

00:55:38.097 --> 00:55:39.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were problems.

00:55:39.807 --> 00:55:44.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But Nehemiah didn’t allow
those problems to rob him of his joy.

00:55:44.812 --> 00:55:47.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We too can be joyful

00:55:47.523 --> 00:55:50.442 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even when we’re under a lot of pressure.

00:55:50.442 --> 00:55:55.447 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our joy doesn’t depend on our circumstances.

00:55:55.447 --> 00:56:00.327 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joy helped Jesus to endure a torture stake.

00:56:00.327 --> 00:56:04.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joy motivated the apostles to keep preaching

00:56:04.081 --> 00:56:06.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even after they’d been beaten.

00:56:06.542 --> 00:56:09.295 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The “joy of Jehovah” can help you

00:56:09.295 --> 00:56:12.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to keep preaching in spite of indifference,

00:56:12.131 --> 00:56:15.801 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
persecution, or any other obstacle.

00:56:15.801 --> 00:56:20.056 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, maybe you feel:
‘Well, that’s what I need.

00:56:20.056 --> 00:56:22.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I need more joy.’

00:56:22.475 --> 00:56:26.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, joy is an aspect
of the fruitage of the spirit.

00:56:26.145 --> 00:56:28.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So when you need more joy,
what do you do?

00:56:28.940 --> 00:56:32.193 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How do you get more of Jehovah’s spirit?

00:56:32.193 --> 00:56:36.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You ask for it: “Father, give me more joy.

00:56:36.739 --> 00:56:39.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I want to be joyful in my service.

00:56:39.367 --> 00:56:41.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I want to rejoice in you.”

00:56:44.122 --> 00:56:48.709 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the beginning of this talk,
we read Psalm 37:4,

00:56:48.709 --> 00:56:53.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we focused particularly
on the first part of the verse,

00:56:53.715 --> 00:56:57.218 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the rejoicing in Jehovah.

00:56:57.218 --> 00:56:59.887 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn to the second part
of the verse now,

00:56:59.887 --> 00:57:02.849 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Psalm 37:4,

00:57:02.849 --> 00:57:07.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and focus on that part for just a moment.

00:57:07.854 --> 00:57:11.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So Psalm 37:4, the first part says:

00:57:11.316 --> 00:57:14.485 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Find exquisite delight in Jehovah,

00:57:14.485 --> 00:57:18.531 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“[and then] and he will grant you

00:57:18.531 --> 00:57:22.494 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the desires of your heart.”

00:57:22.494 --> 00:57:25.830 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What does your heart desire?

00:57:25.830 --> 00:57:29.709 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What are you
looking forward to in the new world?

00:57:29.709 --> 00:57:32.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Is it owning your own home?

00:57:32.671 --> 00:57:36.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In some countries,
it may be just having enough food to eat.

00:57:36.549 --> 00:57:40.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you looking forward to doing work
that you really enjoy?

00:57:40.470 --> 00:57:43.598 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or learning how to do something really well?

00:57:43.598 --> 00:57:45.934 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or maybe you’re older now,

00:57:45.934 --> 00:57:49.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you’re looking forward
to waking up every morning without pain

00:57:49.896 --> 00:57:53.942 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and without wondering,
‘I wonder what this pain means;

00:57:53.942 --> 00:57:56.528 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wonder if I have something serious’

00:57:56.528 --> 00:58:01.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and never, ever having to think
about death again.

00:58:01.533 --> 00:58:04.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you looking forward
to conducting a Bible study

00:58:04.703 --> 00:58:07.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with an unbelieving relative who returns

00:58:07.414 --> 00:58:11.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or maybe with some historical figure?

00:58:11.418 --> 00:58:15.297 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This weekend we learned
that even faithful men of old

00:58:15.297 --> 00:58:18.216 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are going to have to adapt
to a different way of life

00:58:18.216 --> 00:58:20.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and learn how to worship Jehovah in a way

00:58:20.928 --> 00:58:25.015 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that will be acceptable to him then.

00:58:25.015 --> 00:58:27.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“No, Abraham,

00:58:27.518 --> 00:58:32.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that child does not need to be circumcised.”

00:58:32.356 --> 00:58:36.110 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“David, you’re not a king anymore.

00:58:36.110 --> 00:58:41.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you want a glass of water,
you’ll have to get up and get it yourself.”

00:58:41.115 --> 00:58:46.036 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Samuel, I know you’re grateful
to be resurrected,

00:58:46.036 --> 00:58:49.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but we don’t
offer animal sacrifices anymore.

00:58:49.540 --> 00:58:52.501 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“So please, put that knife down

00:58:52.501 --> 00:58:55.921 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and leave that bull alone.”

00:58:55.921 --> 00:59:00.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, there are going to be adjustments
that have to be made.

00:59:00.551 --> 00:59:02.595 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What about living conditions?

00:59:02.595 --> 00:59:05.389 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where would you prefer
to live in the new world?

00:59:05.389 --> 00:59:07.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe you love the country,

00:59:07.391 --> 00:59:10.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and if you’re assigned
to live in the country, you’d be very happy.

00:59:10.311 --> 00:59:14.315 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But suppose you love the country,
but you’re assigned to live in a city?

00:59:14.315 --> 00:59:16.650 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, you can learn to love the city.

00:59:16.650 --> 00:59:19.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah can help you to become

00:59:19.361 --> 00:59:22.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
whatever you need to become.

00:59:22.740 --> 00:59:26.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Whatever you’re given to do
in the new world is going to be a blessing.

00:59:26.702 --> 00:59:29.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah gives ‘good gifts

00:59:29.705 --> 00:59:32.959 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and perfect presents’ to his servants.

00:59:32.959 --> 00:59:35.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And so Jehovah is going to make arrangements

00:59:35.836 --> 00:59:39.924 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that are going to be
for the ultimate good of all mankind.

00:59:39.924 --> 00:59:41.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, we don’t know
what arrangements will be made

00:59:41.926 --> 00:59:44.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to clean up the earth
just after the great tribulation,

00:59:44.804 --> 00:59:47.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but we do know there’ll be work to do.

00:59:47.098 --> 00:59:52.103 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you may have the privilege
of sharing in that.

00:59:52.103 --> 00:59:54.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And think how you’ll feel

00:59:54.731 --> 00:59:58.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as you begin to move closer to perfection

00:59:58.067 --> 01:00:00.695 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
both in mind and in body.

01:00:00.695 --> 01:00:05.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At that time, David’s words
recorded at Psalm 139:14

01:00:05.491 --> 01:00:07.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are going to take on greater meaning.

01:00:07.493 --> 01:00:10.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the last verse
we’re going to read during this convention.

01:00:10.246 --> 01:00:12.248 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’d like you to follow along

01:00:12.248 --> 01:00:15.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Psalm 139,

01:00:15.418 --> 01:00:18.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and verse 14.

01:00:18.671 --> 01:00:23.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now this is imperfect David writing.

01:00:23.551 --> 01:00:26.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Psalm 139:14:

01:00:26.262 --> 01:00:31.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I praise you because in an awe-inspiring way

01:00:31.267 --> 01:00:33.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I am wonderfully made.

01:00:33.686 --> 01:00:36.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Your works are wonderful,

01:00:36.231 --> 01:00:39.275 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know this very well.”

01:00:39.275 --> 01:00:42.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
David was impressed

01:00:42.529 --> 01:00:45.907 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by the way his imperfect body functioned.

01:00:45.907 --> 01:00:48.910 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can you imagine how he’ll feel
when he’s perfect?

01:00:48.910 --> 01:00:52.789 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’ll probably write another song.

01:00:52.789 --> 01:00:57.794 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, how do we
sum up this heart-stirring convention?

01:00:57.794 --> 01:01:01.256 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The best way I can think of is for you

01:01:01.256 --> 01:01:04.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to enjoy one final video

01:01:04.217 --> 01:01:08.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
highlighting the reasons
for joy now and for the future.

01:01:08.305 --> 01:01:10.474 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, enjoy the video,

01:01:10.474 --> 01:01:14.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but pay attention to the music
because we’re going to be singing

01:01:14.102 --> 01:01:16.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that original song
at the end of this program.

01:01:16.730 --> 01:01:19.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We want everyone to sing.

01:01:19.232 --> 01:01:21.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Everyone must sing

01:01:21.985 --> 01:01:25.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—no just moving the lips, no faking.

01:01:25.739 --> 01:01:29.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sing, but enjoy the video as well.

01:01:44.591 --> 01:01:51.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The stars that fill the summer night
Look down from above.

01:01:51.140 --> 01:01:57.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The beauty of the day and night
You fashioned with love.

01:01:57.730 --> 01:02:04.695 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your hands prepared the land and sea,
And ev’rything that came to be

01:02:04.695 --> 01:02:09.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brought joy to your heart.

01:02:12.119 --> 01:02:18.709 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is joy in your creation,
In the message of salvation,

01:02:18.709 --> 01:02:25.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the Paradise to come.

01:02:25.341 --> 01:02:32.348 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But to have your love forever
Is a real and lasting treasure.

01:02:32.348 --> 01:02:45.528 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You alone will prove to be
Our joy eternally.

01:03:00.877 --> 01:03:08.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah, we have all we need
To bring us delight—

01:03:08.593 --> 01:03:15.016 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The things we hear and touch and see
And feel deep inside.

01:03:15.016 --> 01:03:22.148 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You gave us such a perfect start,
Eternity in ev’ry heart,

01:03:22.148 --> 01:03:26.945 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And joy in our lives.

01:03:29.239 --> 01:03:35.745 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
